+#### success_criteria
+- `python scripts/rotate_secret.py --name <n> --value-from-stdin` reads
+  the new value from stdin (never argv — secrets MUST NOT appear in
+  process listings), calls `rotate_secret`, prints
+  `rotated <name> at <iso-timestamp>; prior expires <iso-timestamp>`
+  to stdout, exits 0.
+- Exit codes are explicit: 0 success, 2 invalid args, 3
+  `VaultPermissionError`, 4 any other vault error, 5 empty/missing stdin.
+  Tested via subprocess in `test_rotate_secret_cli.py`.
+- `--dry-run` flag prints "would rotate <name>" and exits 0 without
+  calling `rotate_secret`. Catches: operator typo-protection.
+- `--name` is validated against `^[a-zA-Z0-9_/-]+$` before any vault
+  call; injection-style names raise exit 2.
+- Script has a module-level docstring naming the runbook
+  (`docs/runbooks/secret-rotation.md`) and the spec (`sp001`).
+
+#### edge_cases
+- **Secret on argv.** If anyone passes `--value foo`, the script MUST
+  refuse (exit 2) with a message pointing at `--value-from-stdin`.
+  Catches: secrets in shell history / `ps` output.
+- **Empty stdin.** Stdin closed with zero bytes → exit 5, vault not
+  touched.
+- **Stdin with trailing newline.** A bare `echo "secret" | ...` will
+  feed a trailing `\n`. Strip exactly one trailing newline; preserve
+  any internal newlines (some secrets are multi-line, e.g. PEM keys).
+  Test: `test_cli_strips_only_trailing_newline`.
+- **CTRL-C mid-rotation.** Signal handling: SIGINT during the vault
+  call surfaces as a non-zero exit and the operator sees a clear
+  "rotation may be partial — see runbook" message. Don't swallow.
+
+#### test_plan
+- `test_cli_happy_path_via_subprocess` — pipes a value to stdin, asserts
+  exit 0 and stdout pattern. Catches: argv leak, missing output.
+- `test_cli_refuses_value_on_argv` — passes `--value` flag; expects
+  exit 2 and stderr mentioning `--value-from-stdin`. Catches:
+  regressions that re-introduce CLI value flag.
+- `test_cli_empty_stdin_exits_5` — empty input; vault double records
