+### Task 3: Integration test — zero 5xx during rotation window
+
+#### type
+task
+
+#### effort
+5h
+
+#### depends
+- Task 1
+
+#### files_touched
+- `src/lib/tests/test_vault_concurrency.py`
+- (read-only audit) `src/services/reports/__init__.py`,
+  `src/services/auth/__init__.py`, `src/services/metrics/__init__.py`
+
+#### success_criteria
+- Test starts a synthetic reader loop calling `secret("reports/db_url")`
+  at ~50 req/s for 6 minutes of *simulated* time (via the `_now` seam,
+  NOT real wall-clock 6 minutes — entire test completes in < 10s).
+- During the 6 simulated minutes, the test calls `rotate_secret` at
+  T=60s and asserts:
+  - Zero reader calls raise an unhandled exception.
+  - Every reader call between T=60s and T=360s returns either the prior
+    value `A` or the new value `B` (no `None`, no `""`, no `KeyError`).
+  - The set of values observed by readers includes BOTH `A` and `B`
+    during T=60s..T=360s (proves the overlap is actually overlapping,
+    not flipping instantly).
+  - After T=360s+1, readers see only `B`. Catches: prior-key not
+    expiring on schedule.
+- An import-graph audit asserts that `reports`, `auth`, and `metrics`
+  all import `secret` (not `rotate_secret` or any other write helper)
+  from `acme.lib.vault`. Verified by AST parse, not regex. Catches:
+  any service that opens its own vault client and bypasses the
+  rotation policy.
+- `pytest src/lib/tests/test_vault_concurrency.py -q` exits 0 in under
+  15 seconds. Catches: test that secretly uses real `time.sleep` and
+  takes 6 real minutes in CI.
+
+#### edge_cases
+- **Reader scheduled exactly at flip boundary.** A reader call landing
+  at simulated T=360.000s — define behaviour: gets `B` (new value).
+  Test: `test_reader_at_flip_boundary_sees_new_value`.
+- **Reader scheduled at expiry boundary +1ns.** Reader at T=360.001s
+  with `current` momentarily unreadable falls through to `prior`,
+  which is now expired → KeyError. This is the "tiny window" that
+  would surface as a 5xx in production. The test MUST construct this
+  scenario explicitly and the implementation MUST handle it (single
+  retry on `current` read before falling back, or treat expired prior
+  as "try current once more"). Don't let this slip — it's exactly the
+  bug the AC was written to catch.
+- **Reader cache TTL.** If Task 1 added `vault.invalidate(name)` on
+  flip, assert that a reader holding a cached prior value gets the new
+  value on next call after flip. If not (cache fully avoided), assert
+  there is no module-level cache by inspecting `vault._cache` does not
+  exist.
+- **Service that imports vault under a different name.** AST check
+  must catch `from acme.lib import vault as v` and `v.secret(...)`
+  usage, not just `from acme.lib.vault import secret`.
+
+#### test_plan
+- `test_zero_unhandled_exceptions_during_rotation_window` — 6 simulated
+  minutes, ~18,000 reader calls, zero exceptions. Catches: any code
+  path during overlap that raises (the literal us003 AC).
+- `test_both_values_observed_during_overlap` — set of returned values
+  during the overlap window is `{"A", "B"}`. Catches: rotation that
+  flips atomically (no overlap) — which would still pass "zero 5xx"
+  but violates the spirit of the 5-minute overlap requirement.
+- `test_only_new_value_observed_after_window` — readers at
+  T=360s+1..T=400s see only `B`. Catches: prior key not expiring.
+- `test_reader_at_flip_boundary_sees_new_value` — single reader at
+  exactly T=360s. Catches: off-by-one in expiry comparison
+  (`<` vs `<=`).
+- `test_reader_at_expiry_plus_epsilon_does_not_5xx` — explicitly
+  schedules a reader at T=360s+1ns during a flake where `current` read
+  fails once. Catches: the "tiny race window" 5xx bug.
+- `test_all_services_use_secret_only` — AST audit of three service
+  packages. Catches: a service quietly using `rotate_secret` or
+  bypassing the lib.
